casebody.data:
MANHATTAN TRUST COMPANY vs. MILLER (City Treas., Ironwood), No. 15012.

(Certiorari to Gogebic.)

To compel respondent to pay a certain warrant issued to relator.

The circuit judge granted the writ.

Affirmed November 9, 1895, with costs.

The warrant was payable from the hydrant rental fund, and *1401while respondent answered that there was no money in that fund, it appeared that he had been directed by the common council to transfer a sufficient amount from the general fund to the hydrant rental fund, and respondent contended that such transfer had not been made.
